notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Three fragments of Judeo-Arabic commentary of Yefet ben 'Eli on Genesis.

supportDesc.extent: Part I: Folios 1-14. Part II: Folios 15-73. Part III: Folios 74-83.;

layoutDesc.layout: Part I: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 14; written lines: 14; The unpointed biblical text is embodied, followed by an Arabic translation. Catchwords on every verso. Part II: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; Hebrew text is embodied. Ruled with mastara. Catchwords on every verso. Part III: 1 column(s); ruled lines: 15; written lines: 15; Ruled with mastara. The pointed and accentuated Hebrew text is embodied, accompanied with an Arabic translation. Catchwords on every verso.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Part I: Square and semi-cursive script of 15th century.Part II: Square and semi-cursive script of 15th century.Part III: Square and semi-cursive script of 15th century.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [83v].
